rComments: Love her. She's straightforward, an amazing lecturer, and funny. Engages her students and makes a, in my opinion, very dry subject seem quite interesting.  No secret hidden motives to mess you up on exams. Lab final is *totally* doable, just get your minerals down. Would take her again, wish all proffs were like her

You can get an easy A just by showing up to class and paying attention, and briefly reviewing your notes before the tests. She also posts the power point slides online,so if you just read the slides, it is possible to pass by just showing up to quizzes and tests, but it's a bit harder.

You can get an easy A just by showing up to class and paying attention, and briefly reviewing your notes before the tests. She also posts the power point slides online,so if you just read the slides, it is possible to pass by just showing up to quizzes and tests, but it's a bit harder

Bubbly, hilarious, loves her subject, ask her about it! go to her office hours, she drinks tea usually. Would adopt her. Subject can get confusing and once she get's rolling you have to stop her to make her clarify, which she gladly will. Go to class to learn and be entertained and have qns answered. GO TO ALL THE LABS, non-mandatory but NECESSARY!

This is by far my favorite professor at UCSC. She's very passionate about the topic. She tries her best to keep you entertained and understand the lecture at the same time. One midterm, one final (feat sheet allowed for both) & a project. They're somewhat hard! Quizzes are pretty straight forward, just go to lecture. Not a very stressful class :)
For the mid-term, nothing that's on the test was on the study guide. She's a tough teacher and will make you work for an A. Other than, don't join if you're looking for an easy proffesor

One of my favorite professors at UCSC. Great lectures, shes super funny. 110B was a cool class, if you go to all of the lectures and pay attention its not too hard. No homework, one midterm and a final, a couple quizes. Very approachable

Elise is the sweetest. She's super passionate about the topic and tries her best to make the lectures understandable. They're pretty boring though unless you're super into rocks and stuff... Tests were pretty exhausting and hard, but if you do well in everything else, you'll be fine. Cheat page allowed for both final and midterm. Take it for SI!

Pretty easy going, low stress class. Prof is approachable and seems very willing to help students. She's passionate about her topics. Class can get a little dull sometimes and she tends to screech when she talks. Otherwise easy class, sections are easy but mandatory as every week you have activities. One walking field trip.

Lectures are fun to go to because she trots across the classroom all the time and she screeches when she talks. Tests are alright but she has a great curve and she allows a cheat sheet on them. Sections are mandatory and annoying but they help.

Elise is so funny. She makes lectures interesting because she is so quirky. Lecture material is alittle boring and monotonous but its GenEd so what do you expect? There is a good amount of work in section, but it helps on tests and quizzes. She heavily curves the midterm and final which is nice. She also allows a cheat sheet. Overall,good prof!
Shes cute! I don't attend her lectures and i still passed the class. Just attend her sections and you will be fine.

This class was easy but boring. Didn't go to class half the time because all Knittle does is read off her slides and then post them online, which I am capable of doing myself. I got an A, just go to all the sections and the lectures with quizzes scheduled, study her reviews she posts and you will get an A. Easy boring gen ed.

Elise is really smart and breaks down difficult material so you have a chance at understanding it. Shes really friendly and helpful but will say "you must already know about this so lets move on" in lectures, which can be annoying if you don't already know it! Shes great in giving partial credit and is a very fair grader. Go to lecture.

ugh.really long boring lectures.i used to go at first but then just looked at the power points online.she lets you use a cheat sheet for midterm and final.good amount of work in section but not too bad.dont waste money on the book.

She's such a cutie. I was thinking of being a Geo major, and I took her class last year and it totally inspired me to pursue it. She's very kind and helpful. She's got that nerdy humor that some find funny. Lectures are a little boring but not required. Section is mandatory and very helpful. I highly recommend this class.

Elise is a very interesting teacher. She makes the material much more interesting that one might think through her good examples and witty humor. She explains concepts quite in-depth, and makes the material seem easy. The tests were somewhat hard, but it's still quite easy to get a good grade in the class.

She is an extremely nice and helpful teacher. The material is extremely boring but she is always VERY hilarious & engaging. Midterm is ridiculously hard, but the final is easier. Make sure 2 do the extra credit for the timeline becuz it will really help your grade.It is a lot of work & can b a pain, but is a fairly easy GE. Jayme is a great TA btw!

Knittle is nice, and adds some humor to class and definitely knows her stuff. BUT, the class has waaaaaaaay too much work and the tests are waaaaay too long and fairly difficult, not to mention the annoying quizzes. and half the labs are the most boring thing you'll ever do. unless you are a die hard fan of rocks, DO NOT take this class.
Professor Knittle made understanding a subject I had no idea about pretty easy. She's very approachable and the class is heavily curved; it was worth the knowledge and the GE credit.

A good teacher if you're really into geology, but i strongly believe that if you want to learn about science, take a fundamental science class (chem)instead! That way you can actually learn something instead of memorizing dates and rock names which is completely arbitrary! There should not be so many dumb memorization questions on the midterm!

Very nice teacher.  Lectures were way to long and dry.  I just read the book and got the same information and did just fine.  The tests were difficult but she allows you to use two sides of an 8x11 piece of paper and gives you study questions...do all the study questions and put them on your paper and you will get an A.

I knew nothing about geology before taking this class,and it was easy and interesting.I never once opened the textbook or did any of the reading, I only went to the majority of the lectures.If you don't go to lectures,you can read instead and it's the same thing. The midterm & final were difficult, but HEAVILY curved. Minimul effort and I got an A-

A decent teacher, definitely knows the subject content well, very enthusiastic and tries hard to make the study of rocks interesting, Powerpoint presentations were at times hard to follow and she moves at a fast pace, midterm and final were difficult, however she grades on a curve, put in a little effort and you will get at least a B

I have no interest in the subject, so I found the class boring, but Elise is so sweet and earnest in her efforts to convey the information. Her powerpoints aren't the most organized, but you get the main points and she really tries hard to help students understand!

Interesting class, the book is mostly for labs, so taking lecture notes is important (for the lecture midterm, final). No HW. The lab practical quizzes on 56 minerals (xtal system, chem formula, structure, etc) is about 90% of the grade. Elise is sweet and is good lecturer; I had Erin as a TA and he was OK; I hear Darren is way better.
Elise was a very nice and helpful professor.  Really cares about the students themselves, their needs, and opinions.  Totally recommended!
